HEADWORD: Previse
<hw>Pre*vise"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praevisus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praevidere</ets> to foresee;
<ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>videre</ets> to see. See
<er>Vision</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To foresee.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inform beforehand; to warn.</def> <rj><au>Ld.
Lytton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prevision</ent>⟦br⟧
